{
  "text": "p38 MAPK was further activated by reperfusion in the cytosolic, mitochondrial, and membrane fractions. Although the activation of p38 MAPK by reperfusion is supported by other studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , the finding that reperfusion-mediated activation of p38 occurs in discrete compartments in an in vivo model has not been previously shown. Fryer et al. [CITATION_3] reported no reperfusion-mediated activation of p38 MAPK in the cytosolic fraction in the in vivo rat, but the effect of reperfusion on mitochondrial and membrane p38 MAPK activation was not examined in that study. Activation of p38 MAPK in the membrane fraction during reperfusion is consistent with the findings of Rafiee et al. [CITATION_4] , who found that a considerable activation of this kinase occurred in the particulate fraction of rabbits exposed to chronic hypoxia. These authors (29) also reported a translocation of p38 from the cytosolic to particulate fractions, consistent with our findings of significant changes in the subcellular distribution of this protein in the ischemic zone of the cytosolic, mitochondrial, and membrane fractions compared with the corresponding nonischemic zone. An apparent translocation of p38␣ protein occurred from the cytosolic and membrane fractions to the mitochondria. These alterations in p38␣ expression were not due to cell death because the AMP-579 group exhibited the same changes as the control group despite the lower amount of cell death in the AMP-579 group.",
  "correct_citation": {
